	<Title>
		Recipe: Orange dream
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Orange dream &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Whip up this frothy cooler in minutes &amp;mdash; it tastes like an old-fashioned Creamsicle. For best results, start with ice-cold soy milk and use freshly squeezed orange juice. Creamy, custard-like silken tofu adds extra body. For additional calcium, use calcium-fortified orange juice. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
In a blender, combine the orange juice, soy milk, tofu, honey, orange zest, vanilla and ice cubes. Blend until smooth and frothy, about 30 seconds. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Pour into tall, chilled glasses and garnish each glass with an orange segment. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cups orange juice, chilled&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 cup light vanilla soy milk (soya milk), chilled&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/3 cup silken or soft tofu&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon dark honey&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 teaspoon grated orange zest&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;5 ice cubes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4 peeled orange segments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
